race.comment: LEICA GLOVE (6) lightly raced mare with ability returning from a lengthy break. Created a big impression at her second race start when gapping them over 1200m in a Super Maiden at Coffs Harbour last March.  Ran last at the next start over 1400m at Eagle Farm. Given the two searching trials and makes plenty of appeal. ZIMBARA (7) indicated she was near her peak when holding on gamely from the draw to run fourth over 1200m at Ipswich. Will appreciate the claim from the low draw. Top three player. EAGLE'S FIRE (2) doesn't win out of turn, but the last two runs have been must stronger. Can race closer to the speed and figure prominently. CAPZINZI (4) good effort first up at Grafton but didn't do much last start at a huge quote at Port Macquarie. In the mix.
